cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image processing techniques for analyzing electron microscopy images of metal nanograins. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under cs.MM (Machine Learning). The analysis of the topography of metal nanograins is crucial to nanosensor characteristics, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of Gaussian filters, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the extraction and analysis of curve-type structures, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics).
